HEADWORD: Fangled
<hw>Fan"gled</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>New made; hence,
gaudy; showy; vainly decorated. <mark>[Obs., except with the prefix
<it>new</it>.]</mark> See <er>Newfangled</er>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Our
<xex>fangled</xex> world.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fangleness</ent>⟦br⟧
